&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About General Atlantic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;General Atlantic is a leading global investor with more than four and a half decades of experience providing capital and strategic support for over 830 companies throughout its history. Established in 1980, General Atlantic continues to be a dedicated partner to visionary founders and investors seeking to build dynamic businesses and create long term value. Guided by the conviction that entrepreneurs can be incredible agents of transformational change, the firm combines a collaborative global approach, sector specific expertise, a long-term investment horizon, and a deep understanding of growth drivers to partner with and scale innovative businesses around the world. The firm leverages its patient capital, operational expertise, and global platform to support a diversified investment platform spanning Growth Equity, Credit, Climate, and Sustainable Infrastructure strategies. General Atlantic manages approximately $126 billion in assets under management, inclusive of all strategies, as of December 31, 2025, with more than 900 professionals in 20 countries across five regions. For more information on General Atlantic, please visit: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.generalatlantic.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;www.generalatlantic.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Purpose of Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actis Energy is Actis’ flagship investment program, having raised US$11.2bn across 5 vintages dedicated to critical energy infrastructure assets in growth markets. The strategy focuses on buy-and-build platforms in power generation (both renewable and conventional), distribution, transmission and storage, as well as sub-sectors that contribute to the energy transition. The Actis Energy LatAm team operates from two offices - Austin and São Paulo - with deal teams forming across both to evaluate investments throughout the region. We have an Analyst opportunity, based in Sao Paulo who will be working on screening new investment ideas / strategies, and preliminary / final investment reviews of prospective investment opportunities for the fund. They will also meet and engage actively with project developers, project partners, financial institutions and consultants on matters related to the financial performance of projects and investments as well as assisting a deal leader in all aspects of transaction origination, diligence, execution and asset management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities (this list is not exhaustive)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within an investment team to ensure the greatest impact on value for GA Actis and our investors.&lt;/p&gt;
